overview: The user initiated a request for a comprehensive code review of a
  sleep questionnaire application. The primary goal was to verify that all
  acceptance criteria, as detailed in the project's documentation, were fully
  implemented. The assistant began by thoroughly reading the
  and  files to establish a clear understanding of the
  expected functionality and features. This included identifying core
  functionalities like interactive branching logic, report generation, PDF/CSV
  downloads, and database storage, as well as specific questionnaire sections,
  conditional logic rules, sleep disorder detection mechanisms, and calculated
  metrics. Following this, the assistant systematically reviewed various parts
  of the codebase, including the questionnaire types, validation logic, main
  form component, individual section components (e.g., Daytime, Nightmares,
  Scheduled Sleep, Demographics, Sleep Hygiene), report generation logic, PDF
  generation component, API routes for handling responses and generating
  reports, the admin dashboard, and the Prisma database schema. This detailed
  approach ensured a complete assessment of the application's adherence to the
  documented acceptance criteria.
